The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Chennai, July 15: BPL group patriarch T.P.G. Nambiar today withdrew his petition against son-in-law and BPL Communications CEO Rajeev Chandrasekhar at the company law board (CLB) here following an out-of-court settlement. CLB additional principal bench vice-chairman K.K. Balu ?dismissed? the petition after Nambiar filed a memo with verifying affidavits seeking the withdrawal of the same. 

 New Delhi, July 15: The rate of inflation touched a 22-month low at 4.09 per cent in the first week of July compared with 7.08 per cent a year ago. Cheaper food products led to the decline of the inflation rate, although fuel products became costlier.

 Mumbai, July 15: Bombay Stock Exchange is set to become a corporate entity after August 19. Members today approved the proposal for demutualisation and corporatisation of the exchange.

 New Delhi, July 15: Posco has finally decided to develop a dedicated port at Jatadhari at a cost of $900 million. It will not use the Paradip port due to its low cargo-handling capacity.

 Beijing, July 15: Mittal Steel Co has made its first investment in China, purchasing a 37 per cent stake in state-owned Valin Iron and Steel Co Ltd for $338 million.




